# 🔁 2. ALLOWED TRANSITIONS (MOST IMPORTANT PART)

This is the “rules engine” of your system.

---

# 🟦 A) ONBOARDING FLOW TRANSITIONS

```text id="f1"
IN_PROGRESS → COMPLETED
IN_PROGRESS → FAILED
```

### ❌ NOT allowed:

```text id="f2"
COMPLETED → IN_PROGRESS
COMPLETED → FAILED
FAILED → COMPLETED (unless manual reset logic exists)
```

---

### 🧠 Meaning:

| Transition              | Meaning                          |
| ----------------------- | -------------------------------- |
| IN_PROGRESS → COMPLETED | onboarding finished successfully |
| IN_PROGRESS → FAILED    | onboarding aborted               |

---

# 🟨 B) STEP DATA TRANSITIONS

```text id="f3"
NOT_STARTED → IN_PROGRESS
IN_PROGRESS → SUBMITTED
SUBMITTED → APPROVED
SUBMITTED → REJECTED
REJECTED → IN_PROGRESS (optional retry)
```

---

### 🧠 Meaning:

| State       | Meaning                  |
| ----------- | ------------------------ |
| NOT_STARTED | user hasn't touched step |
| IN_PROGRESS | user filling form        |
| SUBMITTED   | user submitted data      |
| APPROVED    | admin/system approved    |
| REJECTED    | failed validation        |

---

# 🟥 C) APPROVAL TRANSITIONS

```text id="f4"
PENDING → APPROVED
PENDING → REJECTED
```

### ❌ NOT allowed:

```text id="f5"
APPROVED → REJECTED
REJECTED → APPROVED
```

(kept immutable for audit integrity)

---

# 🔄 3. FULL SYSTEM FLOW (REAL LIFE EXECUTION)

This is how everything connects:

---

## 🟢 STEP 1: Role assignment

```text id="s1"
user_roles.is_active = FALSE
```

---

## 🟢 STEP 2: Onboarding starts

```text id="s2"
onboarding_flows created
status = IN_PROGRESS
```

---

## 🟢 STEP 3: Step execution loop

For each step:

```text id="s3"
NOT_STARTED
  ↓
IN_PROGRESS
  ↓
SUBMITTED
```

Then either:

* APPROVED → move to next step
* REJECTED → retry same step

---

## 🟢 STEP 4: Flow completion

```text id="s4"
all steps APPROVED
→ onboarding_flows = COMPLETED
```

---

## 🟢 STEP 5: Decision point

### CASE A — no approval required

```text id="s5"
user_roles.is_active = TRUE
activated_by = NULL (system)
```

---

### CASE B — approval required

```text id="s6"
approvals created
PENDING → APPROVED
```

Then:

```text id="s7"
user_roles.is_active = TRUE
activated_by = admin_id
```

---

# ⚙️ 4. STATE MACHINE RULE ENGINE (HOW YOU ENFORCE IT)

You now enforce rules in **3 layers**:

---

## 🟦 Layer 1 — Database (hard safety)

* FK constraints (steps, flows)
* unique indexes
* triggers (basic validation)

---

## 🟨 Layer 2 — Service Layer (main logic)

This handles:

```text id="l1"
allowed transitions
approval decisions
role activation
step progression
```

---

## 🟥 Layer 3 — Event Layer (optional but powerful)

Events like:

```text id="l2"
on_step_submitted
on_flow_completed
on_approval_approved
```

---

